Based on the Retrieved Chunk, the definition of "Material Adverse Effect" is as follows:

A Material Adverse Effect means a material adverse effect on:

(a) the business, assets or deposit liabilities, properties, operations, condition (financial or otherwise), or results of operations of the party and its Subsidiaries, taken as a whole; or
(b) the ability of the party to consummate the transactions contemplated by this Agreement on a timely basis and in any event on or before the End Date.

Additionally, a Material Adverse Effect also includes:

* A material adverse effect on Parent (measured on a scale relative to the Company);
* A material adverse effect on the Company;
* Materially restricting or imposing a material burden on Parent or any of its Subsidiaries (including, after the Effective Time, the Company and its Subsidiaries) in connection with the transactions contemplated hereby or with respect to the business or operation of Parent or any of its Subsidiaries;
* Events or circumstances inconsistent with any representation or warranty of the Company that has had or would reasonably be expected to result in a Material Adverse Effect on the Company.

This definition applies to the Acquisition Agreement between Columbia Banking System, Inc. (Parent) and Bank of Commerce Holdings (Target).

